Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Looks like the code reads uninitialized memory.

Not a complete deal breaker, but the interface of lnet_inet_enumerate() is extremely ugly. Would it not make sense to define lnet_inetdev like below, and
allocate a properly-sized version of it inside lnet_inet_enumerate()?

struct lnet_inetdev {
	int		li_cpt;
	unsigned int	li_interfaces;
	unsigned int	li_allocated;
	struct {
		u32		li_ipaddr;
		u32		li_netmask;
		char		li_name[IFNAMSIZ];
	} li_info[0];
};
